	intialisation.

2001-06-02 14:41  pgregory

	* libcodegenvm/libcodegenvm.dsp, libcodegenvm/vmoutput.cpp,
	slcomp/slcomp.cpp, slcomp/slcomp.dsp: Minor changes, now outputs
	version properly, and names the .slx file better.

2001-06-02 14:38  pgregory

	* Renderer.dsw: Add new projects libslparse and libcodegenvm

2001-06-02 14:38  pgregory

	* render/: shadervariable.cpp, shadervariable.h: Remove superfluous
	shader type name array.

2001-06-02 14:27  pgregory

	* libslparse/: funcdef.cpp, funcdef.h, ifuncdef.h, iparsenode.h,
	ivardef.h, libslparse.cpp, libslparse.dsp, libslparse.h,
	optimise.cpp, parsenode.cpp, parsenode.h, parser.y, scanner.l,
	typecheck.cpp, vardef.cpp, vardef.h: New library handles parsing of
	a .sl file into a parse tree, which is then exposed to a backend
	code generator via a series of parse node interfaces defined in
	iparsenode.h, ivardef.h and ifuncdef.h.

2001-06-02 14:20  pgregory

	* libcodegenvm/: libcodegenvm.dsp, vmoutput.cpp, vmoutput.h: New
	library handles output of parse tree from libslparse into a format
	suitable for the Aqsis shader VM.

2001-06-02 14:18  pgregory

	* slcomp/: Test.sl, slcomp.cpp, slcomp.dsp: Split functionality
	into separate libraries, libslparse and libcodegenvm.

2001-06-02 14:18  pgregory

	* slcomp/: bison.cc, bison.h, error.h, flexskel.cc, flexskel.h,
	funcdef.cpp, funcdef.h, optimise.cpp, parsenode.cpp, parsenode.h,
	parser.y, scanner.l, typecheck.cpp, vardef.cpp, vardef.h: Moved
	into separate libraries, libslparse and libcodegenvm

2001-05-31 16:07  mbaas

	* render/: imagebuffer.cpp, micropolygon.cpp, stats.cpp, stats.h:
	New statistics output: Number of total gprims the scene consists of
	(after splitting) and the number of culled gprims/grids/micropolys.

2001-05-29 15:20  mbaas

	* render/: imagebuffer.cpp, ri.cpp, shadervariable.cpp,
	shadervm.cpp: Stats values are increased by a method in CqStats
	now.  ri.cpp contains the Start/Stop methods for the various
	timers.

2001-05-29 15:17  mbaas

	* render/: renderer.cpp, renderer.h, stats.cpp, stats.h: Bug fix:
	Statistics variables weren't reset at the beginning of a frame. 
	Moved the time variable and PrintStats() method from CqRenderer to
	CqStats.  Added new timers for shading and individal frame time vs
	total time.  Added methods to increase the counters instead of
	giving out references to them.

2001-05-29 15:14  mbaas

	* render/micropolygon.cpp: Stats values are increased by a method
	in CqStats now.  Bug fix: For motion micropolys the sample hit
	count was increased twice per hit.

2001-05-29 08:38  tburge

	* render/ri.cpp: Changed Gaussian and Sinc to match what PRMan and
	3.2 spec use.  The Sinc filter is windowed by a raised cosine (von
	Hann Window), this additional math matches the PRMan sinc.

2001-05-25 14:38  pgregory

	* libdd/dd.cpp, libddmsock/win32/intel/ddmsock.cpp,
	libddmsock/win32/intel/ddmsock.h: Tidy up the sockets stuff, now
	cleans up after itself better, and ensures that driver processes
	left hanging around (i.e. framebuffer) don't cause problems on the
	next run.

2001-05-24 12:02  tburge

	* render/: attributes.h, ri.cpp: Added attribute storage for two
	matrices needed to convert basis and trying to figure out nicest
	looking way to add it in.

2001-05-24 11:45  tburge

	* render/ri.cpp: Just adding comments about change of basis.  No
	code changed.

2001-05-24 06:23  tburge

	* render/cellnoise.cpp: Ooops, forgot to mention that I removed the
	extra permutation for cellnoiseU,V.

2001-05-24 06:21  tburge

	* render/cellnoise.cpp: Adding a test.	If anyone gets a chance let
	me know if you think the distribution of resulting colors is more
	centered on BMRT and maybe PRMan than my cellnoise function.  PRMan
	and RenderDotC give their noise functions a certain statistical
	property, so maybe cellnoise is skewed a bit to the center too.

2001-05-24 06:17  tburge

	* content/Test/: cellnoise.rib, cellnoisetest.sl: Adding a test. 
	If anyone gets a chance let me know if you think the distribution
	of resulting colors is more centered on BMRT and maybe PRMan than
	my cellnoise function.	PRMan and RenderDotC give their noise
	functions a certain statistical property, so maybe cellnoise is
	too.

2001-05-23 04:30  tburge

	* content/Test/test.bat: Removed @echo off since I keep doing that,
	hopefully no one minds.

2001-05-23 03:07  pgregory

	* librib2/: parser.y, scanner.l: Reintroduce mode switch to allow
	graceful recovery from invalid RIB requests.

2001-05-23 01:51  tshead

	* librib2/tests/Makefile.in: * Makefile.in is a generated file, and
	shouldn't have gotten checked-in in the first place ...

